review_blob: Great IPA that I always find myself going back to. Never had a bad beer from smutty .
A good clean beer but to me weak, high ABV and a 103 IBUs but kind of plain for a double IPA. Good not great.
A very solid Black IPA. Very very tasty and smooth . Bitterness was very nice just enough. Overall very good, but dont let the IMPERIAL fool you its really not, as its only 7.3 %.
If you like Budweiser youll love this. Tastes like a full flavored american corn lager.

A good clean beer, drinking 22oz bomber had it on tap once before, hopheads will be a little disappointed, but a good tasting and clean beer none the less, it just doesnt have a ton of bitterness or hop flavor for an IPA.
beer_name: Berkshire Lost Sailor India Pale Ale

review_blob: An excellent doppelbock very malty and rich, hops are perfect not too sweet but not too bitter, my favorite so far from Gardner Ale house.
Wachusett makes good beer, and this one is no exeption a good porter lots of coffee and a nice dark taste not too dry like some.
